Cheers to better days my friends ! They are - a comin’! I spoke to my sons youth leader today, he is a remarkable young man. 
I asked him if he was scared and he said, “no, I think a pretty cool guy named Jesus has got this”. Good reminder, maybe these messages are from the big man himself. I sometimes wonder that. ? 
The message was clear: 
We either are going to live in a place of fear or faith? Which one will you choose? 
Both demand you to believe something you cannot see. 
Fear cannot exist in the presence of faith. No one should make you fearful because fear = control. 
We don’t know how this will end or how anything will end for that matter. But, if we take a leap of faith fear will soon vanish .
. Stay well and healthy my friends .

insta_description:
We all know by now that hand washing with soap and water for a minimum of 20 seconds is the best way to go when focusing on hygiene. 🧼 Check out the amazing, gentle yet powerful soap made by @floristonsoapcompany to support local business and stay clean! 🏃‍♀️ The pace of life is different every day lately, but sometimes we still need to leave the house and go out in the public. In moments like that, the experts are recommending hand sanitizer as a backup plan.
🛒 Right now, hand sanitizer is really hard to find in #California. Probably everywhere. This, fellow gardeners, is your time to #shine 🌞
🌻 More specifically, it's your #aloevera  plants' time to help you stay moisturized when you make this super easy hand sanitizer recipe! It's definitely more than decorative! 🌱 I used two aloe leaves, trying to guesstimate how much it would take to get 1/3 cup of aloe gel. Wash thoroughly, and let those bad boys drain over a glass or jar. The runny, slightly yellow goo coming out is actually latex, and can be a real irritant to many people's skin, so I let it drip for about half an hour. Washed them again, and peeled off the top and sides of each leaf. Rinse once more to make sure all of the latex is off. 🌿 Now scoop out all of the clear gel that is inside the leaf. Think scooping out and scraping artichoke leaves but with bigger payoff. You want 1/3 cup of the clear slime, or as close as possible. Jiggle it around a bit, then put it in a bowl. 🍶Add 2/3 cup isopropyl alcohol, preferably higher than 70%- some people are using really high proof vodka for this purpose. You can also add scented oils and vitamin E- I did a few drops of the vitamin E I had on hand in the cupboard, and about 10 drops of tea tree oil because it's a good, astringent smell. Blend either with a whisk or in a blender, it's a fast process. Playing with the aloe ratio might help you a bit on thickness if you need more of a jelly consistency. ❤️ Fill up all of your empty containers of #handsanitzer and use freely! Don't forget to water your aloe vera plant too. 😊

insta_description:
My turn to make this post. This unfortunate time has already left a huge impact on countless people. Artists included. While I am sad that our show She Kills Monsters at STAGES was cut one weekend short due to the social distancing/quarantine, I’m not going to pretend that I’m struggling the most because of these cancellations. A countless number of my fellow artists are left without work, without pay for an indefinite amount of time. This is a scary time. But now is the time to support your fellow artists more than ever. We’re all struggling but we’re all going through this trying time together. Let this be a glimpse of how dark and empty the world could be should we lose the privilege of having art in our day to day lives permanently. Stay strong, be safe, friends. Much love.

insta_description:
Коронавирус в ЛА
.
.
Наверное это одна из самых актуальных и обсуждаемых тем. Я не очень люблю поднимать такие вопросы, тем более что эпидемия с новыми видами вирусов происходит чуть ли не каждый год. Но на этот раз по всей видимости что-то другое. Или я просто не помню, чтобы весь мир одномоментно уходил на карантин... Кто-то говорит не поддавайтесь панике, кто-то наоборот настаивает, что лучше «перебдеть» и тут уж конечно каждый для себя выбирает сам. ...Но в ситуации, когда панике поддаются все вокруг и выгребают продукты из магазинов, становится как-то не по себе. Улицы уже практически опустели. А новость о том, что возможна вероятность запрета вообще выходить из дома, навевает на мысли об апокалипсисе. Не мне судить о вирусе, но явно здесь дело не только в этом...ну да ладно. Мысли вслух. 
Берегите себя🙏🏻
.

insta_description:
У Вас было такое что Вы хотите сформулировать мысль и не можете? Вот у меня сейчас именно этот момент. Я хочу рассказать Вам нашу историю о выселении но не знаю с чего начать.😅
Ставь ❤️, присаживайся поудобнее и поехали читать душераздирающие истории. 👉🏼
⠀
Часть 1.  Почему это произошло?
⠀
Конечно не секрет что за неуплату жилья следует наказание, этот рассказ будет об этом.
⠀
Начало февраля, нужно платить за рент $2000, у нас нет этой суммы и мы идём в Leasing office чтобы «договориться». Нам предлагают оплатить минимальную сумму чего мы сделали (около $500) и отставшую внести позже.  Через 5 дней после оплаты на нас подают в суд 😱 Страшно звучит, правда? Но👆🏼 есть много нюансов не в пользу арендодателя.
⠀
Первый момент, не стоит переживать если на Вас подали в суд. Главное найти грамотного переводчика (если Вы не владеете языком) заполнить все предлагаемые Вам формы и отправить их по указанному адресу! ЭТО ВАЖНО! Только после обратной связи у Вас будет возможность оправдать себя на судебном заседании, если же Вы этого не сделаете, то будьте готовы к тому исходу как у нас.
⠀
У нас к сожалению был не столь грамотный в этом деле переводчик и ещё 100500 советчиков сидеть на попе ровно и не париться «с детьми не выселяют, ВЫ ЧЕ». Хочу сказать сразу, мы ездили в компании где должны были предоставить переводчика, но его там не было (так было 3 раза), поэтому приходилось все своими силами.
⠀
😱Нас осудили без нашего присутствия. 02/17/2020 нам на дверь шриф приклеивает решение суда и благополучно уходит. Я успела выйти и только благодаря этому нам удалось с ним поговорить, так бы он просто ушёл.
Он назвал адрес где мы уже были и сказал поехать туда за «помощью» и типа не беспокоиться, все будет супер 👍🏼 В этот день был Present’s day и все было закрыто. Поехал муж 02/18/2020 по тому адресу что сказали и где в очередной раз развели руками со словами «мы ничем помочь не можем». В данном письме было указано решение суда с датой выселения(02/24/2020).
⠀
Продолжение следует.....👉🏼
⠀

insta_description:
E momentul sa va arat cat mai multe fotografii din vacanta mea in America ❤️ In San Francisco cele 20-25 de grade mi-au facut sederea o placere. Oriunde te uitai totul era verde, palmierii se unduiau in vant iar copacii cu origini europene erau in floare, semn de primavara 😍 Dar cum iti dai seama de primavara cand oricum tot timpul e primavara iarna acolo?! Am avut placerea sa o intalnesc si sa o fotografiez pe Alina 🤗 Alina m-a purtat pe toate stradutele acelea de pe dealurile celebre ale San Francisco-ului, printre case victoriene superbe si colorate. Am pornit impreuna dimineata ca sa prindem lumina difuza. Ne-a fost dat sa gasim acest #vwbeetle clasic si am stiut instant ca e cadrul perfect pentru fotografia mea.
Alina e super naturala. Toata fotografia iti transmite asa un aer relaxat si chic. Ah ce mi-as dori sa fiu acolo din nou. #sanfrancisco e orasul meu preferat din America ❤️ Sper sa va inspir cu aceasta serie si sa va reamintesc ca fotografiile in natura sunt minunate si ele 😍

Multumesc Alina 🤗! #oanavedinas #portraitphotography #sanfrancisco #sanfranciscomodel #sanfranciscophotographer #sanfranciscoviews #alwaysgreen #alwaysspring #inlovewithsanfrancisco #vwbeetle #vwbeetlevintage #greenvwbeetle #victorianhouse #greenbackground #california #californiaphotographer #travelerincalifornia #profesionalmodel #portraitphotographer #lifestylephotographer #lifestylephotography.

First off, I’d like to wish everyone health and peace during this COVID-19 pandemic. These are moments when supporting one another and staying calm is essential to making times like these pass by with more ease.
•
“The worst reaction is an overreaction.” -Caputo (Orange is the New Black)
•
City of Beverly Hills has enforced precautions for all non-medical businesses to temporarily close until further notice. It saddens me to have to push back appointments, however, safety is most important. We must do our best in our roles to refrain from potential spreading for the sake of the health of our family, friends and coworkers.
•
Stay safe. Wash your hands frequently, keep safe distances from others. Stay home if you’re not feeling well. Lock your cars and doors at home as people are getting desperate and may commit crimes. Shower when you get home if you were out. Have a daily routine to stay sane during our stays in home.

insta_description:
Day 1 of "shelter in place."
I woke up this morning to this message on my cell phone. I'm glad the county sent it because some people in the Bay Area may have been unaware of the "shelter in place" edict that was handed down yesterday. Not everyone watches the news. For example, my husband doesn't. He relies on me to tell him what's going on in the world. And since he doesn't have a cell phone (he keeps losing them on his fishing trips), he never would have received the text message from the county, either. I guess he's awfully lucky that I'm such a news junkie -- and that I have a cell phone too. 📳🤳😂🤣

Anyone else lay awake at night wondering about the people less fortunate. Do people living on the streets know about the severity of what’s happening? What happens if they all get the virus? What about people who don’t have a car, a babysitter, or money to get groceries? What about the elderly who can’t chance getting out of their house just to go to the grocery store? Or what about the heroes who are working around the clock to make sure we are as safe as we can possibly be. The doctors, nurses, the grocery store employees, the people who are still preparing food at restaurants, and the people delivering it. I set an alarm on my phone to go off at noon every day to remind myself to send out energy, love, prayers, cosmic level protection, and miracles. Add an alarm in yours too if you want to join me. While we still have yet to see how massive this could grow, change starts with us, and often it starts in the mind. Send positivity and shine light wherever you go. .

I got drunk for six days, and on the seventh I remembered I had a job to do. I remembered I was going to go see Hal and find out what he knew about Bixby and Snyder and the deal gone wrong with Jake. I remembered I had to find Bertram and Mary-Lou and figure out what this whole thing was all about. It’s easy to forget your true aim when you have a little bit of cash in your pocket. You become forgetful, lazy, distracted. Enough green can change a man’s life with the snap of the fingers, but in the hands of a fool it fogs his perception. It makes it easier to slip into a stinking abyss of blackouts and vomit, waking to a bog of your own filth, only to drink more and forget the whole mess.

i don’t know much about viruses 🦠. i am just a little pup. but what i know it’s a time many hoomans are in a big stress. 
what i know it’s a time when all of us need to be especially kind to each other. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
• my family got stuck in some situation here in USA too.  our flight back home is canceled and it’s a bigger problem for me to got on a plane to go home wif my hoomans. 
but i am thankful we met people who were ready to help us. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

I feel like I’m in the 90s all over again. Families are taking walks together, and the kids are playing outside.

insta_description:
🇪🇸Mono Lake es un lago grande y poco profundo, de soda salina, que se localiza en el condado de Mono, en el estado de California. Se formó hace al menos 760.000 años atrás como lago terminal de una cuenca sin salida al mar. En el lago se acumula un alto nivel de sales que hacen que su agua sea alcalina. Tiene además altos niveles de arsénico.
¿Sabías que? La NASA identificó en el lago una bacteria (GFAJ-1) de la clase Gammaproteobacteria cuya dieta es pobre en fósforo y rica en arsénico. Es un descubrimiento de gran interés científico, ya que es el primer organismo conocido que puede construir sus componentes celulares utilizando un químico venenoso para cualquier otro.
.
┅ Curioso el dato de la bacteria de este lago, pasamos por el de camino al lago Tahoe y el paisaje vuelve a cambiar. ¿Tenéis alguna anécdota curiosa sobre la fauna de alguno de vuestros viajes? ┅
✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎
🇬🇧Mono Lake is a large, shallow saltwater lake located in Mono County, California. It was formed at least 760,000 years ago as a terminal lake of a landlocked basin. The lake has a high level of salts that make its water alkaline. It also has high levels of arsenic.
Did you know that? NASA has identified a bacterium (GFAJ-1) in the lake, a class of Gammaproteobacteria whose diet is low in phosphorus and rich in arsenic. This is a discovery of great scientific interest, as it is the first known organism that can build its cellular components using a chemical that is poisonous to anyone else.
.
┅ Curious about the bacteria in this lake, we passed by it on our way to Lake Tahoe and the landscape changes again. Do you have any curious anecdotes about the fauna of any of your trips? ┅
.
.

Trading is one of the most specific jobs out there.
.
First of all, the monetary potential is huge.
.
If you know what you are doing, you can literally make thousands in like few days
.
However, there's the other side barely anyone talks about:
.
You could spend whole day trading and still lose money, without good management, DM @invest_with_antoniofx always available to help you manage your account and trades for you.

The point is, unlike with regular jobs, where the more you work - the more you get paid, in trading - the hours you work have nothing to do with how much do you earn.
.
That's a thing to keep in mind.
.
In fact, "trying to work" by forcing trades can very often become counterproductive.
.
You lose money by trading random moves/setups.
.
So, basically, trading is probably the only "job" where, sometimes, you get paid to do simply nothing than invest and sit back watching your money 💰 work for you.
.
Just to sit & wait - for the right opportunity.
.
Even though it sounds easy, many traders will often find it hard to do.
.
Remember - patience is an art!

insta_description:
【Matsumoto】@West Hollywood

結論から言います、凄んごい旨いし、楽しい鮨です。

シャリが旨いとか特定の魚が旨いとかは勿論あるんですが、兎に角、全部素晴らしい。

お店自体はLAには良くある日本食レストランで、お好み鮨もあれば、枝豆や茄子田楽、お肉なんかのメニューもあるみたいで居酒屋さんっぽくもあるんですが、omakaseで鮨をお願いすると、これが素晴らしい。

松本大将はLAに来て20年くらい経つそうなんですが、何と、料理の世界に入ったのはこちらに来てからとか。LAには野沢大将という伝説の鮨職人さんがいて、既に引退されて現在は2代目が新しい形でお店を引き継いでらっしゃいますが、松本大将はその野沢大将の系譜だそうです。東京で言えば新橋鶴八一門みたいな感じかと。ちなみに今や世界中でomakaseと呼ばれる様になりましたが、どうやらこの言葉、野沢大将がアメリカで鮨を広める過程で馴染んだ言葉の様で、その真髄はtrust me（大将が旨いもん出すから信頼しろ）と言うことだ、と説明されていたみたい。

その系譜たる松本大将のomakaseは、東京で言う鮨匠系みたく酒肴と鮨が交互に出てくるスタイルで、これが変化に富みつつ、例えば青魚だったり炙りものだったりをグルーピングして出して頂けて、次は何かな〜、とワクワクします。

鮨も酒肴も、日本料理や江戸前の仕事を巧みに取り入れた素晴らしいもので、構成も素晴らしく、加えて日本酒のラインナップもかなり渋いです。

少し驚いたのは炙りにAMGHバーナーを使って居られました。LAでは日本で言う消防法みたいな法律下、室内で炭火を使うことが難しい一方、現地の方々はやはり魚の皮目には抵抗があったりするので、ガスバーナー炙りは必須ですが、どうしてもプロパン臭が気になります。AMGHバーナーはこれを解消してくれるものの、入手も容易ではないし、値段も可愛くないのですが、恐らく現時点でLAでは松本大将くらいしか使って居られないと思います。

いやはや、この研究熱心具合、脱帽です。仕事のひとつひとつに拘りと情熱を感じました。そりゃ旨い筈です。 ◯のれそれ 三杯酢＋茗荷

🇪🇸Calico es un pueblo fantasma ubicado en el Condado de San Bernardino, California, Estados Unidos. Se encuentra en las montañas Calico, en el desierto de Mojave. Fundado en 1881 como una ciudad minera de plata, actualmente es un parque estatal llamado Pueblo Fantasma de Calico. Unas letras gigantes con el nombre del pueblo nos dan la bienvenida. Walter Knott adquirió Calico en la década de 1950 y restauró todos los edificios de la ciudad, exceptuando 5 de ellos que permanecen con su arquitectura original, para que lucieran como en la década de 1880.
¿Sabías que? Calico fue declarada en 2005 por el entonces gobernador, Arnold Schwarzenegger, como La Ciudad Fantasma de la Fiebre de la Plata.
.

🇬🇧Calico is a ghost town located in San Bernardino County, California, USA. It is located in the Calico Mountains in the Mojave Desert. Founded in 1881 as a silver mining town, it is now a state park called Calico Ghost Town. Giant letters with the name of the town welcome us. Walter Knott acquired Calico in the 1950's and restored all the buildings in the town, except for 5 of them which remain with their original architecture, to look like the 1880's.
Did you know that? Calico was declared in 2005 by the then governor, Arnold Schwarzenegger, as The Ghost City of the Silver Rush.
.
┅ And I was late... it was already closed and I could only see it from the outside. Has that ever happened to you guys? Arriving at a place and not being able to see it because of the time? ┅

🇪🇸El árbol de Josué (Yucca brevifolia) es una especie de árboles de la familia de las Asparagaceaes. En primavera estos árboles se cubren de flores blanco-amarillentas.
Si logra sobrevivir al desierto, puede llegar a vivir unos doscientos años. El árbol más alto del Joshua Tree National Park tiene unos 13 metros de alto.
¿Sabías que? Su nombre le fue dado por un grupo de mormones que a mediados del siglo XIX, los vieron por primera vez. La forma peculiar de este árbol les recordó la historia bíblica del patriarca Josué levantando sus manos hacia el cielo, implorando la ayuda de Dios.
.

🇪🇸El valle de la Muerte es un valle desértico ubicado al sureste de California, Estados Unidos, en el desierto de Mojave. En verano es uno de los lugares más calurosos del mundo, junto con los desiertos de África, Australia y Medio Oriente. Se distribuye de norte a sur a lo largo de 225 km. Durante la década de 1850, se extrajeron oro y plata en el valle. En la década de 1880, el bórax fue descubierto y extraído.
¿Sabías que? El valle recibió su nombre en 1849 durante la Fiebre del oro de California, por los buscadores y otros que intentaron cruzar el valle en su camino hacia los campos de oro, después de que 13 pioneros perecieron en una expedición temprana de trenes de carretas.
.
┅ No he viajado a la luna pero creo que Death Valley es lo más parecido que tenemos en la Tierra, me parece espectacular y totalmente diferente a cualquier otro lugar. ¿Conocéis Death Valley? ┅

🇬🇧Death Valley is a desert valley located in southeastern California, United States, in the Mojave Desert. In summer it is one of the hottest places in the world, along with the deserts of Africa, Australia and the Middle East. It is distributed from north to south along 225 km. During the 1850s, gold and silver were mined in the valley. In the 1880s, borax was discovered and mined.
Did you know that? The valley was named in 1849 during the California Gold Rush, after prospectors and others who tried to cross the valley on their way to the gold fields, after 13 pioneers perished in an early wagon train expedition.
.
┅ I haven't traveled to the moon but I think Death Valley is the closest thing we have on Earth, I think it's spectacular and totally different from any other place. Do you know Death Valley? ┅

🇪🇸Devil’s Golf Course es una gran salina situada dentro Del Valle de la Muerte. En su localización existía un lago que cubría el valle a una profundidad de 30 pies (unos 9 metros), que se secó hace unos de 2.000 a 4.000 años, dejando en toda la zona minerales disueltos y esculpidos que, durante miles de años, han ido dando lugar a formas fantásticas.
¿Sabías que? Su nombre proviene del libro de guías del Servicio de Parques Nacionales de 1934, en el que se menciona la frase de que “sólo el diablo podía jugar al golf” en su superficie, debido a la textura rugosa de las grandes formaciones de cristal de sal de halita. Poco después, la salina llegó a ser conocida como el Devil’s Golf Course o lo que sería el Campo De Golf Del Diablo.
.
┅ Y la naturaleza me sigue sorprendiendo como la que más. ¿Qué os parece este lugar? ┅
✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎
🇬🇧Devil's Golf Course is a large salt flats located within Del Valle de la Muerte. In its location there was a lake that covered the valley to a depth of 30 feet (about 9 meters), which dried up about 2,000 to 4,000 years ago, leaving dissolved and sculpted minerals all over the area that, for thousands of years, have been giving rise to fantastic shapes.
Did you know? Its name comes from the 1934 National Park Service guide book, which mentions the phrase that "only the devil could play golf" on its surface, due to the rough texture of the large halite salt crystal formations. Shortly thereafter, the salt mine became known as Devil's Golf Course.
.
┅ And nature still surprises me the most. What do you think of this place? ┅
.

🇪🇸Otra de las caminatas que puedes realizar en Death Valley es Golden Canyon. La ruta que sube por el Cañón Dorado es gradualmente ascendente a través de un pasillo rocoso con altas paredes doradas. El camino comienza en un sendero señalizado con estacionamiento en Badwater Rd., justo al sur de Furnace Creek. Después de una milla (1,6 km.), se llega al cruce con el sendero Gower Gulch, y de este punto a la cima del cañón y Red Cathedral.
¿Sabías que? Si sois de trekking más extremos, podéis preguntar en el centro de visitantes por el trail del Telescope Peak, de 22,5 km. y 914 m. de elevación y por el Wildrose Peak, de 13,5 km. y 670 m. de elevación.
.
┅ Dicen que las vistas desde la cima de Golden Canyon son espectaculares, yo no hice este trail, el calor era sofocante. ¿Habéis hecho algún trail con un final espectacular? ¿En qué lugar? ┅

🇬🇧Another walk you can take in Death Valley is Golden Canyon. The route up Golden Canyon is gradually ascending through a rocky corridor with high golden walls. The trail begins on a marked trail with parking on Badwater Rd, just south of Furnace Creek. After a mile (1.6 km), you reach the junction with the Gower Gulch trail, and from this point to the top of the canyon and Red Cathedral.

🇪🇸Badwater es una cuenca endorreica localizada en el Parque Nacional del Valle de la Muerte. Destaca por ser el punto más bajo de América del Norte, con una profundidad de 86 m por debajo del nivel del mar. El agua forma lagos temporales tras las tormentas, el agua se evapora, los minerales se concentran y quedan únicamente las sales.
¿Sabías que? El monte Whitney, el punto más elevado en los 48 estados, se encuentra a solo 120 km. hacia el oeste.
.
┅ Mi sensación al ver esta zona por primera vez fue que el suelo estaba cubierto de nieve, según te vas acercando te das cuenta de que es sal, una capa con una profundidad de metro y medio de dam, increíble. ¿Qué os parece Badwater? ¿Os resulta tan impresionante como a mi? ┅

🇬🇧Badwater is an endorheic basin located in Death Valley National Park. It stands out as the lowest point in North America, with a depth of 86 m below sea level. The water forms temporary lakes after storms, the water evaporates, the minerals concentrate and only the salts remain.
Did you know that? Mount Whitney, the highest point in the 48 states, is only 120 km to the west.
.
┅ My feeling when I first saw this area was that the ground was covered with snow, as you get closer you realize that it is salt, a layer with a depth of meter and a half of dam, incredible. What do you think of Badwater? Do you find it as impressive as I do? ┅

🇪🇸Artist's Drive se encuentra en Badwater Road. El inicio del recorrido está claramente marcado, y la duración es de unos 45 minutos, dependiendo de las paradas. Artist Palette es un área en la cara de las Montañas Negras conocida por la variedad de colores de sus rocas.

.

🇬🇧Artist's Drive is located on Badwater Road. The start of the tour is clearly marked, and the duration is about 45 minutes, depending on the stops. Artist's Palette is an area on the face of the Black Mountains known for the variety of colors of its rocks.
Did you know that? Artist Palette's colors are caused by the oxidation of different metals: iron compounds produce red, pink and yellow, the decomposition of mica derived from tuff produces green, and manganese produces purple.

🇪🇸En Salt Creek, donde el agua dulce se convirtió en agua salada cuando el lago gigante se secó hace unos 10.000 años, podemos encontrar el curioso pupfish (pez cachorro) de Salt Creek, un pez de 6,4 cm de largo (2 pulgadas), que no vive en ningún otro lugar.
¿Sabías que? Esta especie de pez tiene la capacidad de sobrevivir en el agua desde temperaturas cercanas al punto de congelación hasta casi 108°F/42°C, además de en agua 4 veces más salada que el océano. Con el calor del verano, los peces se quedan dormidos.
.
┅ Es muy curioso ver a estos pequeños peces nadando tranquilamente en una especie de charca en medio del desierto, no dejéis de verlos si visitáis Death Valley. ¿Y vosotr@s? ¿Habéis vivido algo único con la fauna en alguno de vuestros viajes? ┅
✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎
🇬🇧In Salt Creek, where fresh water became salt water when the giant lake dried up about 10,000 years ago, we can find the curious Salt Creek pupfish, a 2 inch long fish that lives nowhere else.
Did you know that? This species of fish has the ability to survive in water from near-freezing temperatures up to about 108°F/42°C, as well as in water 4 times saltier than the ocean. In the heat of summer, fish fall asleep.
.
┅ It is very curious to see these small fish swimming quietly in a kind of pond in the middle of the desert, do not miss them if you visit Death Valley. And you? Have you lived something unique with the fauna in one of your trips? ┅
.
.
.
.
.

🇪🇸Dentro del Parque Nacional de Death Valley, en el Furnace Creek Museum, podemos encontrar una diligencia, equipo de minería y transporte, uno de los dos únicos vagones originales supervivientes del Equipo de las Veinte Mulas, artefactos de los días de los pioneros, la Vieja Dinah (un tractor de vapor y vagón que reemplazó a los Equipos de las Veinte Mulas), y una Locomotora Baldwin 280 de la era minera del Valle de la Muerte, 1885-1927, locomotora histórica que se utilizaba para el transporte de bórax.
¿Sabías que? El bórax es un mineral que se encuentra principalmente en dos lugares del planeta: Turquía y el desierto de California.
.
┅ Cuando viajo, me encanta conocer datos históricos del lugar que visito e imaginarme cómo sería el día a día de todas esas personas. ¿Y vosotr@s? ¿Os gusta dejar volar vuestra imaginación cuando viajáis? ┅
✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎
🇬🇧Inside Death Valley National Park, in the Furnace Creek Museum, we can find a stagecoach, mining and transportation equipment, one of the only two original surviving wagons of the Team of Twenty Mules, artifacts from the days of the pioneers, Old Dinah (a steam tractor and wagon that replaced the Twenty Mule Teams), and a Baldwin 280 Death Valley mining era locomotive, 1885-1927, historic locomotive used to transport borax.
Did you know that? Borax is a mineral found mainly in two places on earth: Turkey and the California desert.
.
┅ When I travel, I love to learn historical facts about the place I visit and imagine what the day-to-day life of all those people would be like. What about you? Do you like to let your imagination run wild when you travel? ┅
.
.
.
.
.

insta_description:
🇪🇸Para que las dunas existan debe haber una fuente de arena, vientos dominantes que la muevan y un lugar para que se recoja. Sólo hay unas pocas zonas en Death Valley en las que la arena está "atrapada" por accidentes geográficos como las montañas. Las Mesquite Flat Sand Dunes son las más conocidas y fáciles de visitar, localizadas cerca de Stovepipe Wells. Aunque la duna más alta se eleva sólo unos 30 m. (100 pies), las dunas cubren una vasta área. Este campo de dunas incluye tres tipos: crecientes, lineales y en forma de estrella.
¿Sabías que? El sandboarding sólo está permitido en las dunas de Mesquite y prohibido en el resto de dunas para proteger plantas y animales sensibles.
.
┅ La imagen de desierto que tenemos con dunas dista mucho de Death Valley, hasta que llegamos a este punto, donde el paisaje cambia. ¿Qué os parece? ¿Os gusta el desierto? ┅
✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎ ✈︎
🇬🇧 For the dunes to exist there must be a source of sand, dominant winds to move it and a place for it to be collected. There are only a few areas in Death Valley where the sand is "trapped" by geographical features such as mountains. The Mesquite Flat Sand Dunes are the best known and easiest to visit, located near Stovepipe Wells. Although the highest dune rises only about 30 m. (100 feet), the dunes cover a vast area. This field of dunes includes three types: crescent, linear and star-shaped.
Did you know that? Sandboarding is only allowed on the Mesquite dunes and prohibited on the other dunes to protect sensitive plants and animals.
.
┅ The image of desert we have with dunes is far from Death Valley, until we get to this point, where the landscape changes. What do you think? Do you like the desert? ┅
.
.
.
.
.

insta_description:
Si hablamos del exequatur como procedimiento judicial, es aquel procedimiento que tiene por objeto reconocer la validez de una sentencia dictada por un Tribunal extranjero y por tanto permitir su ejecución en un Estado distinto del que se dictó la misma.

El procedimiento de exequatur se encuentra regulado en la Sección II "De las Sentencias dictadas por  Tribunales Extranjeros" del Título VIII "De la ejecución de las Sentencias" de la Ley de Enjuiciamiento Civil de 1881 en los artículos 951 a 958. Asimismo en el ámbito de la Unión Europea, cuando se trate de reconocer y ejecutar una Sentencia dictada por un Tribunal de un Estado miembro de la Unión Europea, se aplica el Reglamento (CE) 44/2001 del Consejo, de 22 de diciembre de 2000, relativo a la competencia judicial, el reconocimiento y la ejecución de resoluciones judiciales en materia civil y mercantil, y el Reglamento (CE) 2201/2003 del Consejo de 27 de noviembre de 2003 relativo a la competencia, el reconocimiento y la ejecución de resoluciones judiciales en materia matrimonial y de responsabilidad parental, por el que se deroga el Reglamento (CE) 1347/2000.

Si necesitas información adicional o asesoría para la gestión de dicho trámite, consúltanos de formoline y te ayudaremos. ⤵️

insta_description:
I use this page as a bit of a travel diary, so I post most of my pictures in real time. However, in light of this horrible virus affecting the entire world, people are now self-isolating/social distancing to protect families, communities and the NHS. So as it looks like we’ll be staying put for a bit, I’ll be posting archive pictures of some of my favourite places from my living room in London. 
Not going to lie, I’ve never really been a “stay home” person (unless I’m hungover), but trying my best not to get cabin fever. It’s also made me realise I took travelling for granted, especially Europe where we’re lucky to be able to hop on a plane and be somewhere in an hour. 
For the next few weeks I’ll bring a little bit of the world to your feeds, and hopefully we can look forward to holidays and social events in the not so distant future and appreciate them even more🤞🏽. For now - take care and don’t be a greedy toilet roll or pasta hogger (I still don’t get this btw, will you die if you don’t have 24 rolls of toilet paper though?!) anywayyyy I’m kicking off my self isolation series with San Diego. What a beaut.

insta_description: I have never been to Palm Springs before and wasn’t expecting much, but boy was I wrong! I knew, of course, of Indian Wells Open 🎾and Coachella music festival (i mean, Queen B and her Homecoming movie🎤🙌🏼), but the small towns that surround Palm Springs have SO MUCH to offer! Restaurants, entertainment, national and state parks, art, history... just few of the things I would like to experience again in PS. Palms Springs is also noted for late 70s and early 80s residential architecture w/ straight lines that can be seen all over residential neighborhoods. And a lot of residents have just stunning doors! From shapes and sizes to vibrant colors - all can be seen in this desert landscape. 🌵The neighborhood of these houses - all of them - is super FLAT, with little to no traffic. Sidewalks are in AWESOME shape, completely #wheelchair friendly!

insta_description:
サンフランシスコ・ベイエリアでついに出た外出自粛令、4/7まで。
生活必需品の買い物や、家族での散歩はOK（周りの人と2メートル離れるという条件付き）、公園遊びは人との接触が多くなるのでNG。
公立の小中高はすべて休校。息子の幼稚園はひとクラス12名に縮小して継続。うちは自宅で面倒見れるので、しばらくお休みになりました。
必要最低限の職種を除き、基本は在宅勤務に。
レストランやカフェはテイクアウトやデリバリーのみ、UberEatsやDoorDashもOK。
公共交通機関は継続。食料品店、ガソリンスタンド、薬局はオープン。Amazonも遅配や品切れなどありつつも、普通に届きます。
ちなみに違反した場合は罰則もあります。

3月初め頃から、いつかは外出禁止になると言われてきましたが…これだけの大規模な規制、準備にかなりの時間が必要なはずなのに、それをいきなりズバッと発令して12時間後に実施するだなんて。日本では絶対に見られない行政のスピード感、危機管理能力の高さを思い知らされました。
いつも役所の対応とかグダグダで、この国ホントに世界の超大国なのか？と何度も思ったけど…アメリカの底力を見た感じ。

写真は今日の散歩の様子。帰り道、お腹が空いたと30分泣き叫ばれ、周りの人から哀れみの目で見られました…2メートル離れた所から…😅
#普段から人がいないので #違いがよくわからない #shelterinplace #sanjose #california

accessibility_caption: Image may contain: 1 person, closeup
insta_description:
English below👇🏼
.
Trucco ispirato dalla bellissima @erikabarbato, semplice, naturale e leggero. 👸🏼 Sapete ormai quanto adoro il make-up, e seppure sto passando molto tempo a casa, mi fa sentire meglio avere un aspetto decente.
La quarantena non è obbligatoria qui a Los Angeles (non ancora), ma ho deciso comunque di restare a casa il più possibile, perché credo sia la mossa più Intelligente al momento. Mi sembra abbastanza logico che ciò prevenga la contaminazione l’un l’altro. Questi giorni lavoro tanto dal PC, parlo spesso con amici al telefono e pulisco casa stile Cenerentola. 
Voi come passate il tempo al di là di computer, telefono, TV e cucinare?
.
I did some light makeup today because I was bored at home, and I had the gorgeous @erikabarbato as an inspiration. She did a makeup tutorial a few days on light makeup perfect for home if you still want to feel put together, which I always do.
Quarantine is not mandatory in LA as of now (although it is in San Francisco for 3 weeks), but I still decided to stay home as much as I can, to avoid to catch it. I’ve had pneumonia a few times in my life, and the feeling of not being able to breath was painful and horrible; I don’t want it again.
So the past 3 days I’ve spent them working from my laptop, cleaning the house, talking to friends on the phone.. and eating LMAO. I did do some light exercise though. What do you guys do beyond watching TV or being on an electronic device?
.

Who has mad love for Santa Monica?
.

I’ve been before, but spending a few nights made us all fall in love and it’s safe to say that it’s now our favourite area in LA 🎡 .
.
Riding a bike along this coastline is such a bucket list thing to do, so we were delighted when we found out our hotel @fairmontmiramar #hosted 🌊 just a few hundred metres from the famous pier, has a selection of bikes for their customers 🚲 They even have children’s bikes and protective gear! .
.
Travelling is amazing, but every now and again you have these really wow times together and this evening was one of them. We parked our bikes up, had a blast on all the attractions and watched one of the most incredible sunsets we’ve ever seen. .
Santa Monica and @fairmontmiramar thank you for an incredible time, we will be back 🙌🏼😍 #OnlyAtTheMiramar

insta_description:
In the middle of difficulty lies opportunity.
#losangeles #california #eatoncanyon #america 
世の中はなんだか大変なことになっていて
明日寝て起きたら
何もかもなかったことになってないかな…
なんて思ったりするけど

みんなが変わらず元気でいて欲しいと
心から願います

ついにこちらロサンゼルスも休校になり
子供達と過ごす2日目、
早くもシワが増えた気がします😤

宿題もオンライン授業もないので
学校と同じタイムスケジュールで
なんしー校長がカリキュラムを決めてるんだけど
何かにつけて褒美がないと不満を垂れる我が子

この子達、
アメリカの学校で完全に餌付けされてるな…
これをやったら先生はクッキーくれるとか飴くれるとか
”成果が可視化されるシステム“にどっぷり浸かってやがる

気合いと根性の昭和育ちの私は理解に苦しむが
褒美にママのとびっきりの笑顔を〜♡
って言ったら一瞬時が止まった気がした( ꒪⌓꒪)
飴ちゃんにしとこか…

いやいや、そんなことを伝えたいんじゃない
伝えたいことがあるんだby小田和正

コロナで休校になった娘に
“今自分にできること”を考えさせてみた
すると
「子供オンライン英会話」
やってみようかと！
同じくらいの年の子と英語でのお喋り♩
英語に興味がある、
習った英語を話してみたい、
なんてお子さんがいましたら
ぜひご連絡くださ〜い😃

insta_description:
On Wednesday, March 11, California prisons stopped visits in an effort to combat the spread of coronavirus.
CDCR said that the move was a precaution and that there had been no confirmed cases in the sprawling system. “CDCR values visitation as an essential part of rehabilitation, but at this time the Department must make difficult decisions in order to protect the health and wellness of all who live in, work in, and visit state prisons,” the statement said.

Yet prison staff will likely bring COVID-19 into the prisons without knowing they are infected. Given the extremely contagious nature of COVID-19, along with its high infection rate, it is thus likely to spread quickly throughout the prison population. 
As Sr. Helen Prejean states, social distancing is impossible in the prison system - leaving our loved ones on the inside vulnerable to being infected and susceptible to serious injury and possible death. 
We must advocate for the early release of non-violent and elderly inmates to ensure that our prison populations stay as safe as possible during this time. 🙏🏽 #sisterhelen #sisterhelenprejean #cdcr #california #covid_19 #covid19 #coronavirus #earlyrelease #staysafeyall #pursuitofjustice ⚖️

accessibility_caption: Image may contain: one or more people, people standing, bridge, sky, ocean, outdoor and nature
insta_description:
The first thing we did in San Fransisco was don some rather fetching helmets and cycle the Golden Gate Bridge.

We cycled all the way from Fishermans Wharf through Crissy Field under and on to the bridge (be prepared for those hills 😰). Cycling the bridge itself was quite a surreal experience. It felt so strange that suddenly we were actually really here, and really doing this. And for the time you're on the bridge it's just you and your thoughts and the REALLY loud wind as once you're on there, it's almost impossible to stop. So even when you're together it's an experience you take in completely by yourself.

The best part of the whole cycle ride was coming off the bridge and down the huge hills into Sausalito. We laughed the whole way down and you really do pick up some speed 🚴‍♀️ 💨
.
Of course, this is such a classic thing to do when visiting San Francisco and it's with good reason.

I think as a first time visitor this is just as important to do as discovering all the infinitely cool neighbourhoods (which we will get to way later) and I would definitely recommend this as the first thing you do. It's amazing to get the views of the bridge, from all angles, including on it and also views back of the city skyline. It has this constant feel of "omg we are really here!" the whole time. Plus, anything is better on bikes 🤙🏻
.
.
*** Boring but useful info: We rented our bikes from Blazing Saddles on Hyde Street. This is the easiest point to get from a rental place to the waterfront where you aren't cycling with traffic but on a dedicated bike path. I would fully recommend doing it this way and it also provides the most scenic route.

However, one thing to point out is, that despite how anally I research everything there was confusion with the ferries back from Sausalito to San Fransisco. The majority were going to the Ferry Building and I didn't want to cycle that far back through the city. We waited (and wasted a lot of time) for one headed to Fisherman's Wharf and you still have a cycle on the city roads from here (or you could walk your bike), however, I was surprised that cycling it was completely fine! Take whichever ferry arrives first and cycle back ***
location.name: Crissy Field San Francisco

Harmonia Studio ile tanışmam, Arina Alakoç ve Elena Dalgic tarafından düzenlenen bir çıkış uygulamasına sahip olan mutlu bir fırsat sayesinde başladı. Muhtişdi ve sonra Arina ile Yoga Iyengar bireysel bir yaklaşımla- başıma geldi. Harmony Studio, belirli bir şey için geldiğiniz yerdir ve beklenen sonucun fazlalığı ile elde edersiniz, her seferinde bana olan sey ! Bu stüdyoda olduğu gibi Ahenkli bir yerde sabunumu sunma fırsatım olması ne büyük bir nimet 🍀

Началось мое знакомство со Студией Harmonia благодаря счастливому случаю, попав на выездную практику организованной Arina Alakoç и Elena Dalgic. Это было мощно, а потом со мной случилась Йога  Айенгар с Ариной, с индивидуальным подходом. Студия Гармония это то место, куда приходишь за чем-то определенным, а уходишь со сверх ожидаемым результатом, так происходит со мной каждый раз!

【🎊沼津店12周年記念グランヴァンイベント第二弾🎊】
．
ヴィノスやまざき沼津店も今年で12周年‼️
今回は、カリフォルニアで最も著名な蔵元の一つ「オーパス・ワン」のセカンドワインが登場😵
．
①オーヴァチュア NV (¥30,000＋税)
「カリフォルニアの父」と称されるモンダヴィ氏と、ボルドー・メドックの格付けシャトーを持つロスチャイルド家がタッグを組み創設された「オーパス・ワン」🏰
今回は、その本家よりもさらに生産量が少ないセカンドラベル「オーヴァチュア」をご用意しました❣️
18ヶ月の樽熟成・複数ヴィンテージのブドウをブレンドしており、なめらかなタンニンとコクのある味わいを早くからお楽しみいただけます😊
．
②ストーンヘッジ トロフィー・プレミアム カベルネ・ソーヴィニヨン 2017 (¥7,800＋税)
高騰化が激しいナパ・ヴァレーにおいて、コストパフォーマンスの高いワインを造り人気を集めている「ストーンヘッジ」
こちらは、米国農産物ホールオブフェイムの殿堂入りを果たした記念に造られた、彼らのプレミアムワイン😲
ナパヴァレーの中でも標高が高い「アトラス・ピーク地区」のブドウを使用🍇
日夜の寒暖差が激しいことで、力強くも華やかな、メリハリある赤ワインに仕上がっております✨
．
------------------------------------------------
日程：3月27日(金)〜3月29日(日) 12:00-20:00
開催場所：ヴィノスやまざき沼津店店内(イーラde地下1階しずてつストア内)
参加費：一般¥2,900(税込) 会員¥2,400(税込)
．
ご予約はこちらから💁‍♂️💁‍♀️
TEL：055-954-4550
MAIL：numazu@v-yamazaki.co.jp
------------------------------------------------

It was one of our first Chinese/ Vietnamese Wedding and we learnt so much about their traditions and also got to meet the most brainiac people all under one roof! Just to name a few friends of theirs, there was a doctor who is also a florist ( @floralrebellions ), to the surgeon who also made the beautiful wedding cake! ( @cakeday_tuesday )

insta_description:
We need more conscious tourists
💔
By• @tbwabackslash 
Thousands of insta-happy tourists annihilate a California town in pursuit of the perfect pic.

Over 50,000 people flooded into the town of Lake Elsinore over the weekend to get pictures of the town’s incredible super bloom of poppies. Visitors trampled flowers and created hours-long traffic jams that led to the town barring access to Walker Canyon, one of the popular spots for the poppies.

This is hardly the first time Instagram has “ruined” photo friendly destinations. Last year a Canadian sunflower farm, Bogle Seeds, shuttered its doors to photographers after thousands of selfie-takers trampled its flowers. Earlier this month residents of Rue Crémieux in Paris sought to ban Instagrammers who have been making living there “hell.” The tense relationship between tourism, nature and social media is coming to a head and “Instagrammable” no longer necessarily means good for business.

accessibility_caption: Image may contain: plant, sky, outdoor and nature
insta_description:
Lunghe distese di terreno pianeggiante puntellate da cespugli e cactus filiformi che si protendono verso il cielo. Un caldo secco che massaggia ogni muscolo del tuo corpo e sanguinanti tramonti pastello all'orizzonte.
Un silenzio così profondo che ti sorprenderai che qualsiasi piccolo movimento, persino il luccichio delle stelle, non echeggi intorno a te.
Il tempo trascorso in quel posto riesce a donare un senso di concentrazione, felicità e calma che difficilmente riuscirai a provare nella vita. 
È come premere il pulsante Reset nella tua mente che ti permetterà di lasciare il deserto con occhi più chiari e gentili con cui guardare il mondo e sentendo l’energia pulsare nelle vene. 
È un posto fatto di magia, di questo ne sono certa, hai la sensazione che il tempo si fermi. Bastano due giorni a farti chiedere se siano passati mesi, anni o solo pochi attimi. E arrampicatevi, arrampicatevi su qualsiasi roccia possibile. 
Molte sembrano imponenti, ma basta avvicinarsi per scoprire che Madre Natura ha letteralmente lasciato le pietre miliari per raggiungere la cima. Saltellare tra una roccia e l’altra vi farà sentire proprio come delle formiche su un marciapiede. 
Anche 24 ore sono sufficienti per tornare in contatto con sé stessi. C’è senza dubbio qualcosa in quelle stelle brillanti e nelle ore trascorse a vagare sotto il sole vibrante, qualcosa che mi fa sempre voler rimanere un po’ di più in quella magia.

insta_description:
Dio, come mi sento spossato, indebolito.
Quel giorno, al Joshua Tree, devo rubare un'altra Tachipirina al buon Gianluca.
Ma ostinato come sono, curioso come un bambino, non riesco proprio a stare chiuso in auto e così salgo su una delle montagne che circondano i campi desertici del parco nazionale. Che è un bellissimo posto. Non fosse che tra le attrazioni principali ci sono alcune rocce dalle forme sinuose, fatte di granito. Ve lo posso giurare, sembrava di essere a San Pantaleo o a Santa Teresa, esattamente qui in Gallura! Quindi, avvezzi come siamo alla visione del granito in tutte le sue forme, abbiamo presto dirottato su altre zone del parco, come questa.
Foschia sulle città, laggiù all'interno, in una vista panoramica interessante.
Fujifilm X-H1

insta_description:
Meet baby 🐱 Lisyen! Look at her beautiful color! Like it?
_______________________________
Знакомьтесь с малышкой Лисьен! Такое имя выбрала ее хозяйка😊🙂, благодаря Вашим вариантам. Посмотрите, какой у нее красивый окрас 😍. Стрелки, бровки, эракез - прям бьюти блогер!

А вообще сегодня тема пойдет о странности 🙄 людей. Я смирился с тем, что новым подписчикам - нужно с чистого листа все объяснять. Но меня пугают люди, которые давно за нами следят и до сих пор не осознали моей позиции 🍽о питании. Некоторые пишут - можно я заплачу, а Вы мне скажете каким кормом Вы кормите своих?

Я всегда и везде доношу - мне все-равно, чем Вы будете кормить своего 🤷🏼‍♂️ питомца. Потому что он Ваш питомец и Вы в ответе за его жизнь, а не я. Мне хватает более десятка своих. Но если Вы не можете справиться с одним, тогда добавить нечего.

Нельзя услышать из рекламы, от друга и т.п. - это "ЛУЧШИЙ* корм и бежать его покупать. Так можно просто навредить питомцу. Ну на лучший расклад ввести в расстройство пищеварения, в аллергию и т.д.

Верный вариант - уточнить рацион питания с ветеринаром ✅ или у заводчика, где приобреталось животное (а не у другого). Только они могут правильно подобрать, учитывая все необходимые параметры кота (вес, возраст, хронические заболевания органов, кожи и шерсти, состояние пищеварительной и репродуктивной систем, ротовой полости, наследственные особенности, индивидуальную непереносимость и чувствительность к компонентам корма). Почему я должен брать на себя ответственность, за Ваше животное дистанционно? Чтобы потом получить порцию 💩, если что не так?

А еще круче, когда поступают письма 2 дня/месяца 💰 назад купил котенка в питомнике *название* подскажите, чем кормить, как в туалет приучить и т.д. - Вы серьезно? 🤨 Это должен рассказать все Ваш заводчик. А наша общая информация доступна в постах и эфирах. Зачем тогда приобретали питомца в этом питомнике, если Вы не соблюдаете его рекомендации? Или не хотите лишний раз 🤐 тревожить? - куплю там, а вырстит "Деборкадер" - отличная схема.

insta_description:
Another #ritualmurder . In fact, the #crash occured in the intersection between the 16th Street and #Yucaipa Road in the county of #SanBernardino , #California . St. Bernardino created the holy monogram, which later became the symbol of the #Jesuits .The sum of the digits of the date is 16, the #tower in the tarots. 1,2 miles away from this intersection, the transmission tower is located, in Dunlap Boulevard. Dunlap was the publisher of a #book titled “ #GoldenDawn “in 1930. According to Yucaipahistory , Yucaipa can mean “crying place” and was influenced by the Mormons.Moreover, Brino was a #star in the #movie “ #7thheaven “and in Templar’s #DivineComedy written by Dante the 7th heaven is associated with Saturn, very important for occultists. Brino was driving a #ToyotaCamry and camry means #crown , the first sephirot of the Kabbalah.__
Un altro omicidio rituale. Infatti, l’incidente in cui ha perso la vita #LorenzoBrino è avvenuto all’incrocio fra la 16a strada e la strada Yucaipa nella contea di San Bernardino, in California. S. Bernardino ha creato il monogramma sacro, poi divenuto il simbolo chiave dei #Gesuiti . La somma delle cifre della data è proprio 16, la torre nei tarocchi. A 1,2 miglia dal luogo dell’impatto c’è una torre trasmittente, sita nella strada dedicata a Dunlap, pubblicatore di un #libro intitolato “Golden Dawn” nel 1930. Gli abitanti locali di Yucaipa narrano che la loro città significa “luogo del pianto” ed è stata influenzata dai Mormoni. Inoltre, Brino era una stella del #film “settimo paradiso”. Nella templare/rosacrociana #DivinaCommedia di Dante, il settimo paradiso è associato a Saturno, molto importante per gli occultisti. Brino era al volante di una Toyota Camry, dove Camry significa corona, la prima sephirot della cabala.

📷 and notes by @hansc008 
This is the first time I'm trying the Mayacamas 1990.
The Durand made sure that I got out the cork in one piece. I decanted this bottle for around 3 hours. 
The nose had red cherries, raspberries, spices, leather, licorice and a hint of oak.
It is full bodied with some firm grippy tannins still present.
There's a good amount of acidity with enough fruit, a good minerality and a little spiciness to complement.
At 30 years of age this is still a youthful and vibrant wine.
While already drinking well, I think it will keep improving with more age.
One of the best Napa Cab imo. @mayacamaswine

insta_description:
💫Olivia Steele
🌎US .

Olivia Steele, a Berlin based American artist whose work in neon and signs have been gaining a lot exposure, works within the spiritual and philosophical, at times using natural elements, fabric and found objects. This is a departure from the raw and the visceral motifs that often define neon artists works. Steele makes work that lends itself to public installations and outdoor interventions, artwork that has a dialogue and interaction with their surroundings. In Steele’s own words, “my art is not about what I see… Its about what I invite you to see.”
.

The pieces have a resonance, which impact the viewer on an existential level, asking questions as well offering affirmations. They are also deeply personal, expressing the innermost desires and aspirations of the artist.

In times like this, Everything you need is inside you, hopefully helps us find what we are looking for.

So here's the thing. Negativity is heavy and it will weigh you down. It will drain you, exhaust you and trick you into believing that hope is merely a figment of your imagination and a waste of your time and positive energy. 
By not nurturing your positive energy it becomes vulnerable to manipulation. 
But negative energy is a part of life and rather than succumbing to it or fearing it we must confront it. Don't hide from it, don't avoid it, don't let it get the best of you. It is greedy with an insatiable appetite for your spirit and once your spirit becomes compromised so does your sanity. You must remember to stay grounded. This is why rest and recuperation are so important, so that you can regain your strength and your focus. In return your clear mind will shield you from disillusionment and you will see clearly that hope is very real. 
PS Keep practicing social distancing please.
